<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="68" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,1089,1238,1582]" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,361,1238,1262]" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
Together with 
<taxonomicName authority="Bezděk, 2005" authorityName="Bezděk" authorityYear="2005" box="[518,650,1238,1262]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Apophylia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cervenkai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[518,650,1238,1262]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">A. cervenkai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[656,737,1238,1261]" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Bezděk, 2005" authorityName="Bezděk" authorityYear="2005" box="[787,868,1238,1262]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Apophylia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kaffa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[787,868,1238,1262]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">A. kaffa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[874,958,1238,1261]" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Allard" authorityYear="1889" box="[967,1089,1238,1262]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Malaxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vernallis">
<emphasis box="[967,1089,1238,1262]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">A. vernallis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forms a group of very similar species which can only be distiguished in male sex, using the structure of the aedeagus. The apex of aedeagus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Allard" authorityYear="1889" box="[643,764,1302,1326]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Malaxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vernallis">
<emphasis box="[643,764,1302,1326]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">A. vernallis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is produced and slightly asymmetrical to the left (
<figureCitation box="[318,382,1334,1358]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[151,190,1164,1183]" captionTargetBox="[185,1092,220,1131]" captionTargetId="figure-136@4.[185,1092,220,1131]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 6-8. Apophylia vernallis (Allard, 1889). 6 – aedeagus (a – dorsal view; b – lateral view); 7 – last ventrite of female; 8 – male metatarsus. Scale: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5174142" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5174142/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
), while it is symmetrical in 
<taxonomicName authority="Bezděk, 2005" authorityName="Bezděk" authorityYear="2005" box="[671,752,1334,1358]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Apophylia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kaffa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[671,752,1334,1358]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">A. kaffa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[758,839,1334,1357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[851,927,1334,1358]" captionStart-0="Figs 1-5" captionStart-1="Figs" captionStartId-0="2.[151,187,1077,1096]" captionStartId-1="4.[151,190,1164,1183]" captionTargetBox-0="[185,1092,220,1046]" captionTargetBox-1="[185,1092,220,1131]" captionTargetId-0="figure-241@2.[185,1092,220,1046]" captionTargetId-1="figure-136@4.[185,1092,220,1131]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="4" captionText-0="Figs 1-5. Apophylia nobilitata Gerstaecker, 1871. 1 – aedeagus (a – dorsal view; b – lateral view); 2 – last ventrite of female; 3 – last ventrite and pygidium of female, lateral view; 4 – male metasternum; 5 – male metatarsus. Scale: 1 mm (Figs 1-3 and 5); 2 mm (Fig. 4)." captionText-1="Figs. 6-8. Apophylia vernallis (Allard, 1889). 6 – aedeagus (a – dorsal view; b – lateral view); 7 – last ventrite of female; 8 – male metatarsus. Scale: 1 mm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5174140" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5174142" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5174140/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5174142/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
) and asymmetrical to the right in 
<taxonomicName authority="Bezděk, 2005" authorityName="Bezděk" authorityYear="2005" box="[318,450,1366,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Apophylia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cervenkai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[318,450,1366,1390]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">A. cervenkai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[457,540,1366,1389]" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[553,632,1366,1390]" captionStart="Figs 1-5" captionStartId="2.[151,187,1077,1096]" captionTargetBox="[185,1092,220,1046]" captionTargetId="figure-241@2.[185,1092,220,1046]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-5. Apophylia nobilitata Gerstaecker, 1871. 1 – aedeagus (a – dorsal view; b – lateral view); 2 – last ventrite of female; 3 – last ventrite and pygidium of female, lateral view; 4 – male metasternum; 5 – male metatarsus. Scale: 1 mm (Figs 1-3 and 5); 2 mm (Fig. 4)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5174140" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5174140/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
